Rule: Higher education levels (Masters or Prof-school) significantly increase the likelihood of earning more than $50k a year.
While being in a Blue-Collar job can still lead to earning more than $50k, occupations in Sales or Service may also be associated with higher earnings.
The number of working hours per week does not show a clear pattern in determining the income level, as both negative and positive outcomes include similar working hours.
Marital status alone does not appear to be a strong determinant of income level, as "Single" status appears in both negative and positive outcomes.
